<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="70" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,518,761]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
Perennial herb, 
<quantity box="[316,428,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="cm" value="52.5" valueMax="100.0" valueMin="5.0">5–100 cm</quantity>
tall, stems succulent, green or purplish. Leaves petiolate; petioles 
<quantity box="[1188,1315,518,545]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="8.1" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="cm" value="4.1" valueMax="8.1" valueMin="0.1">0.1–8.1 cm</quantity>
long, nodal wings 
<quantity box="[210,324,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="7.1" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="7.1" valueMin="0.0">0–7.1 mm</quantity>
wide; lamina ovate or elliptic, 0.8–17.7 × 
<quantity box="[802,923,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" metricValueMax="16.0" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="cm" value="8.2" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="0.4">0.4–16 cm</quantity>
, laciniate, deeply lobed to pinnatisect with 1–7 pinnae, margins dentate to serrulate. Sepals ovate, 2–10 × 
<quantity box="[809,906,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="1.0">1–7 mm</quantity>
, green to purple. Corolla bright yellow, 4–29 × 
<quantity box="[136,289,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0699999999999998" metricValueMax="1.95" metricValueMin="0.19" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="10.7" valueMax="19.5" valueMin="1.9">1.9–19.5 mm</quantity>
; stamens with upper theca 
<quantity box="[597,733,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2.5 mm</quantity>
long, lower theca aborted, connective 
<quantity box="[1174,1310,626,653]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3499999999999996" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="2.3499999999999996" valueMax="4.1" valueMin="0.6">0.6–4.1 mm</quantity>
long, dorsal protuberance present or absent. Capsules ovoid, 
<quantity box="[679,772,662,689]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="70" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,518,761]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,698,724]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Distribution:</emphasis>
—Central Mexico to north 
<collectingCountry box="[668,729,698,724]" name="Chile" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Chile</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[790,901,698,724]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="70">Argentina</collectingCountry>
between (0) 
<quantity box="[1047,1213,698,725]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" unit="m" value="2450.0" valueMax="3900.0" valueMin="1000.0">1000–3900 m</quantity>
. Introduced in other countries from Europe and Asia (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Molau, U." box="[551,689,734,760]" pageId="9" pageNumber="70" pagination="595 - 615" refId="ref6610" refString="Molau, U. (1981) The genus Calceolaria in NW South America. VIII. The section Calceolaria and appendices to parts I-VIII. Nordic Journal of Botany 1: 595 - 615. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1756 - 1051.1981. tb 01419. x" type="journal article" year="1981">Molau 1981</bibRefCitation>
, p. 606).
</paragraph>
